		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Yeah, it looks suprisingly good! They did a really good job on the interface. <br /><br />The minimap/lookaround solution seems unique/visionary, even if it is derived from the problem of porting the game to a console with a feature set not designed with this type of game in mind.<br /><br />It would have fared better if flashROM had been a commercially viable thing for the NES. Apparently it was <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Flash_memory" class="postlink">invented by a toshiba employee</a> in 1980 and made available in 1984, but must've cost a lot.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
