	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">FrankWDoom wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">do they say in the video it has 2x 32K ram? or where did you get that from? I don't have audio at work.</div><br />MMC5 is presumed from the 8x8 attributes.<br /><br />Further presuming that 8k WRAM is not enough space to save the city state, there's no 16k chip (but you can do 2x8k), so the next size up is 32k. The MMC5 supports 2x32k (64k) at maximum.<br /><br />So I think lidnariq is either presuming this maximum 64k of WRAM (2x32k), or presuming 32k WRAM and 32k CHR-RAM (could do pattern RAM banking). I'm not sure which.<br /><br /><br /><s>SNES SimCity had 256k RAM inside it, for comparison, which could save two cities, so that might put an assumption for 64k WRAM being necessary into perspective.</s><br /><em>Edit:</em> never mind, it was 256 kilo<em>bit</em>, so 32k.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


